The paper deals with lower bounds on the running time of algorithms for graph problems, specifically on graphs of bounded treewidth. This suggests that the paper could belong to categories related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and graph theory (cs.GT). Among these, cs.DS and cs.CC seem to be the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on lower bounds for algorithmic problems and assumes the Strong Exponential Time Hypothesis. However, cs.CG, cs.DM, and cs.GT are also possible categories, as the paper deals with graph problems and their properties.
